                                 ======
                                 gitary
                                 ======


A diary using a Git repo as a backend.


Installation
------------

gitary is a Bash script and relies on the following external tools:

    - GNU coreutils
    - GNU grep
    - Git

If you're on Arch Linux, you can use the following AUR package:

    - https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/gitary-git/


Running
-------

If you're running gitary for the first time, you must initialize your
data directory:

    $ cd "$XDG_DATA_HOME"
    $ mkdir gitary
    $ cd gitary
    $ git init

You can then run the program from any directory:

    $ gitary

Refer to the manpage for all options.
